🔹 a) Basic Recording using Toolbar

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Create a Blank Process
Step 3: Go to the Design tab (Top Ribbon)
Step 4: Click on Recording
Step 5: Select Basic

Step 6: Choose the application window where you want to record
Step 7: Perform actions like:

click button
type text
select menu

Step 8: Click Save & Exit after recording

Result:
UiPath automatically generates activities like Click, Type Into, Select Item

🔹 b) Basic Recording using Notepad

Step 1: Open Notepad on your computer
Step 2: Open UiPath Studio
Step 3: Go to Design → Recording → Basic

Step 4: Select the Notepad window

Step 5: Click inside Notepad and type:

Hello UiPath

Step 6: Stop recording by clicking Save & Exit

Result:
Workflow will contain:

Click activity
Type Into activity
🔹 c) Desktop Recording using Toolbar

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Go to Design tab
Step 3: Click Recording
Step 4: Select Desktop

Step 5: Choose desktop application/window

Step 6: Perform actions like:

open file
click menus
enter text
use keyboard shortcuts

Step 7: Click Save & Exit

Result:
Desktop recording creates a container activity with multiple actions inside

🔹 d) Desktop Recording by Creating a Workflow

Step 1: Create a New Sequence / Workflow
Step 2: Drag Open Application activity

Step 3: Indicate the desktop application
Example: Notepad

Step 4: Inside Do container, drag activities like:

Click
Type Into
Hover

Step 5: Add required actions manually

Step 6: Run the workflow

🔹 e) Web Recording
Example: Find movie rating from IMDb website

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio
Step 2: Go to Design → Recording → Web

Step 3: Open browser with IMDb website
Example: IMDb

Step 4: Click on search bar

Step 5: Type movie name
Example:

"Inception"

Step 6: Press Enter

Step 7: Click on movie result

Step 8: Use Get Text activity to extract rating

Step 9: Store output in variable rating

Step 10: Use Message Box to display:

rating
🔹 f) Web Recording Manually

Step 1: Create a New Sequence
Step 2: Drag Use Application/Browser activity

Step 3: Indicate browser window

Step 4: Drag Type Into activity
Select search box

Step 5: Enter text:

"Inception"

Step 6: Drag Click activity
Click search button

Step 7: Drag Get Text activity
Select rating text

Step 8: Store in variable rating

Step 9: Drag Message Box
Enter:

rating

Step 10: Run the workflow
